==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flyover
<hw>flyover</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the upper level of a
crossing of two highways at different levels; called in the United
States an <altname>overpass</altname>; <as>as, an overpass is called a
<ex>flyover</ex> or a flypast in England</as>.</def>
<mark>[Brit.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> overpass, flypast.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a low-altitude flight (usually of military aircraft)
over spectators on the ground.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> flypast.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flypaper</ent>⟦br⟧
